## 🔟 Remediation Recommendations

### Immediate Priority (Critical):

| # | Vulnerability | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | SQL Injection | Use parameterized queries |
| 2 | SQLi Auth Bypass | Input validation + prepared statements |
| 3 | XSS Stored | Output encoding + CSP headers |
| 4 | Admin Panel Exposed | Implement RBAC |
| 5 | FTP Directory Exposed | Disable public access |
| 6 | Broken Access Control | Server-side authorization checks |
| 7 | SQLi in Login | Parameterized login queries |

### High Priority:

| # | Vulnerability | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | No Account Lockout | Rate limiting + lockout policy |
| 2 | Weak Password | Enforce strong password policy |
| 3 | XSS Reflected | Input sanitization + output encoding |
| 4 | Sensitive Data | Remove phpinfo.php |
| 5 | Default Credentials | Change all defaults immediately |
| 6 | Weak Session IDs | Cryptographically random session IDs |
| 7 | JWT Token | Store in HttpOnly cookies |
| 8 | Credentials in URL | Use POST method for login |

### General Recommendations:

- Implement Web Application Firewall (WAF)
- Regular security code reviews
- Automated vulnerability scanning
- Security awareness training for developers
- Implement proper logging and monitoring
- Use HTTPS for all communications
- Regular penetration testing schedule
- Follow OWASP Secure Coding Practices

