## 1️⃣1️⃣ Conclusion

This penetration test successfully demonstrated the importance of
web application security testing. A total of 15 vulnerabilities
were identified and exploited across DVWA and OWASP Juice Shop
using the OWASP Top 10:2025 framework.

### Key Takeaways:

1. SQL Injection remains one of the most critical vulnerabilities
   and can lead to complete database compromise

2. Authentication weaknesses allow attackers to bypass login
   mechanisms entirely using simple techniques

3. XSS vulnerabilities can persist in databases affecting all users

4. Security misconfigurations expose sensitive files and admin panels
   that should never be publicly accessible

5. Proper access controls are essential to prevent privilege escalation
   and unauthorized data access

